07:53.440 --> 08:01.680
But you can never mathematically prove exactly what shape the original whole onion was before I took a knife to it.

08:01.760 --> 08:03.780
Oh, that is a brilliant way to put it.

08:04.000 --> 08:04.140
Yeah.

08:04.180 --> 08:06.620
Is that what sphere pop is doing to equations?

08:06.820 --> 08:07.740
That's exactly it.

08:07.900 --> 08:11.020
The intact onion is your unevaluated nested bubble.

08:11.440 --> 08:14.380
It has a specific unrecoverable architecture.

08:14.820 --> 08:15.120
Right.

08:15.120 --> 08:19.680
When you chop it, you commit it to a configuration that you can never restore.

08:19.960 --> 08:21.560
You cannot un-chop the onion.

08:21.720 --> 08:24.380
The scaffolding of its original layers is gone.

08:24.600 --> 08:26.980
The chopped pieces are the final output,

08:27.400 --> 08:31.940
